      "text": "What is true is that competition using money and fair and open markets is a historically tested and relatively effective mechanism to minimise many forms of corruption. But so was a poultice a relatively effective way to combat infection for hundreds of years before we discovered antibiotics. This is not a robust argument to say that we cannot create better forms of \"social greed\" using cryptography, social networks, mobile phones and a more advanced understanding of economics and social behaviour than we had in the middle ages - when the current system of social cooperation based on markets was evolved."
